speech.p:
asked the Home Secretary (1) how many aliens have been permitted to enter, and to remain in, this country since 1st March, 1938, and how many have been refused this permission; and how these figures compare with other European countries;

(2) how many aliens have been given permission to take up employment or to set up in business for themselves, either professionally or otherwise, in this


country since 1st March, 1938; how many aliens have been refused this permission; and how these figures compare with other European countries?
